  "prompt": "How do I get an internship at IITs in December?",
  "response": "Securing an internship at one of the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) can be a highly rewarding experience, offering exposure to cutting-edge research and industry practices. However, internships at IITs can be competitive, and timing is crucial, especially if you're aiming for a December start. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you navigate the process:\n\n### 1. **Understand the Timeline and Availability**\n\n- **Academic Calendars:** Most IITs follow academic calendars where internships (often referred to as \"research assistantships\" or \"industrial internships\") are typically arranged during the summer months (June to August) or semester breaks. December internships might fall into shorter holiday periods or align with specific projects.\n  \n- **Availability:** Check if the specific IITs and departments you are interested in offer internships during December. Some departments may have ongoing projects that require assistance year-round, while others may have fixed internship periods.\n\n### 2. **Identify Your Area of Interest**\n\n- **Research Areas:** Determine which IITs and departments align with your academic background and career aspirations. IITs are renowned for a variety of fields, including Engineering, Computer Science, Biotechnology, Physics, and more.\n\n- **Specific Labs or Projects:** Identify specific labs, research groups, or professors whose work resonates with your interests. Having a clear focus will make your application more targeted and effective.\n\n### 3. **Prepare",
